  "original_title": "Sri Lanka schedules power cuts of 3 hours for August 27, 28",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka schedules power cuts of 3 hours for August 27, 28",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Power cuts of three hours of will be imposed around Sri Lanka on August 26 and August 27, 2022 Public Utilities Commission (PUCSL) Chairman Janaka Ratnayake said.",
        "All areas (A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, I, J, K, L, P, Q, R, S, T, U, V and W) will have power cuts of 1 hours and 40 minutes between 01.00 pm and 06.00 pm and 1 hour 20 minutes from 06.00pm to 10.00 pm on Saturday 27 and Sunday 28.",
        "Group CC will experience a 2 hour and 30-minute power cut from 6.00 am to 8.30 am.",
        "Groups MNOXY will have a 3 hour power cut from 5.30 am to 8.30 am.",
        "The PUCSL had previously attempted to curtail power cut durations and provide uninterrupted power supply on holidays, but a sudden breakdown in the Norochcholai power plant extended durations again.",
        "The state-run Ceylon Electricity Board (CEB) said supply interruption time and restoration time will vary within 30 minutes as indicated above. (Colombo/ Aug 25/2022)"
      ],
